title: For Sale:  Smith and Wesson Model 659 9MM
postcontent: Offered here is my Smith and Wesson 659. For those not familiar with the Smith and Wesson Model 39 and 59, the 659 is a stainless version of the Model 59. These are some of the first “Made in America” that were both single action and double action. A live round can be carried in the chamber with the safety on (the hammer is blocked) and all that is required to fire is flip the safety up and pull the trigger. This 9MM has a double stack magazine (1 supplied) that holds 14 rounds. Since it is all steel, there is much less felt recoil than some of today’s polymer framed pistols. The ambidextrous safety is supplied for either right or left hand shooters. I have added the Rosewood grips, standard plastic grips are included. There are some light scratches from holster wear over the past 20+ years but does not affect the operation of the pistol. This is one outstanding pistol to add to your collection.
